{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:17:10.186366+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:jRRipL | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e1ca30c972e01292ca37220f3425c823916d34fc)", "id": "lc_6a7ebdaa-a7ab-408b-b67f-65b1998ca57f"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:jRRipL | #!/usr/bin/env bash\n| MCP:jRRipL | \n| MCP:jRRipL | set -o errexit\n| MCP:jRRipL | set -o pipefail\n| MCP:jRRipL | set -o nounset\n| MCP:jRRipL | \n| MCP:jRRipL | (cd mobile && flutter build apk && flutter build ios)\n| MCP:jRRipL | \n| MCP:jRRipL | (cd mobile/android && fastlane internal)\n| MCP:jRRipL | (cd mobile/ios && fastlane beta)\n| MCP:jRRipL | (cd web && ./deploy.sh && firebase deploy)", "id": "lc_afde477e-86c7-4a8a-8ed1-75146eb600f2"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f233928b-5125-41df-9b7a-d5f9b99b265f", "tool_call_id": "call_84fd02e50e234c9b9eeed227", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:17:34.577194+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's what I found. There's an important detail to flag first:\n\n---\n\n### Important: This is **not** a Flutter web project\n\nThe README and project structure make clear that inKino is a **multiplatform** Dart app with two separate front-ends:\n\n| Target | Tech | Directory |\n|---|---|---|\n| Android & iOS | **Flutter** | `mobile/` |\n| Progressive Web App | **AngularDart** | `web/` |\n\nThe web app uses the Dart SDK and the **`webdev`** toolchain (AngularDart + `build_runner`), *not* Flutter's web renderer. There is no `flutter build web` step.\n\n---\n\n### Exact shell commands (in order)\n\nAll commands below assume you are in the **repository root**.\n\n#### (a) Install the web tooling\n\nPer the README's \"Development environment setup\" section:\n\n```bash\n# Install the standalone Dart SDK (not the one bundled inside Flutter)\n# See https://dart.dev/get-dart\n\n# Install webdev, the build/serve tool for Dart web projects\npub global activate webdev\n```\n\n> The README also mentions installing Flutter, but that is only needed for the `mobile/` Flutter project — it is **not** required for the web build.\n\n#### (b) Fetch dependencies\n\nDerived from `ci-script.sh` (lines 5–9):\n\n```bash\n# 1. Rename the missing TMDB config sample so the project compiles\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\n\n# 2. Fetch packages for core (shared business logic)\ncd core && pub get && cd ..\n\n# 3. Fetch packages for the web project\ncd web && pub get && cd ..\n```\n\n#### (c) Produce a release web build\n\nDerived from `web/deploy.sh`:\n\n```bash\ncd web && webdev build\n```\n\nThis runs the AngularDart `build_runner` in release mode and writes the compiled output to **`web/build/`** (not `build/web/`).\n\n---\n\n### Summary (single script)\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -e\n\n# (a) Install tooling\npub global activate webdev\n\n# (b) Fetch dependencies\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\ncd core && pub get && cd ..\ncd web  && pub get && cd ..\n\n# (c) Release build\ncd web && webdev build\n```\n\n**Note on output path:** `webdev build` produces its output under `web/build/`. If you need it at the repo-root level as `build/web/`, you would need to move/rename the directory afterwards (e.g., `mkdir -p ../build && mv build ../build/web` from inside `web/`).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 819, "prompt_tokens": 16203, "total_tokens": 17022, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 218, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 14784}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "f544ee847d7d46f08240eff5d565bf17", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead63-5aaa-77b0-9fd2-cd44427005bb-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 16203, "output_tokens": 819, "total_tokens": 17022, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 14784}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 218}}}}]}}}
